A former deputy governor of Kwara, Chief Simon Sayomi, is dead.  His son, Ola confirmed his death in a telephone interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday in Ilorin. According to him, the former deputy governor died in his hometown, Igosun in Oyun Local Government Area of the state. Ola said that his father died after a brief illness. “He died on Wednesday night between 9:30 p.m. and 10:p.m. He was born on Oct. 10, 1925. “We will miss him because he was a hero to us in everything,” he said. Sayomi was the deputy governor of the state from 1999 to 2003 under the administration of late Muhammed Lawal. The duo lost their re-election bid to Dr Bukola Saraki during the 2003 governorship election.  (NAN) LOKOJA - The first civilian governor of Kwara, Alhaji Adamu Attah, is dead. Attah, aged 83, died on Thursday in his Abuja residence after a protracted illness. A prince of Ebiraland, the late Attah was a lawyer by profession and was a former Federal Permanent Secretary. He was buried in… May 1, 2014 In "News" Kano -  The death has occurred of the former Deputy Governor of Kano State, Alhaji Magaji Abdullahi. Aged 69, Abdullahi died in the early hours of Sunday after a protracted illness at his residence located at NNDC Quarters at Sharada area in Kano metropolis. Alhaji Abdulkadir Ibrahim, the former Press… July 24, 2016 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko  Abuja – (Sundiata Post) -   President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has expressed grief over the demise of former Oyo State Governor, Abiola Ajimobi. Lawan reinded that late Senator Ajimobi served with merit at the upper legislative chamber between 2003 and 2007 during which time he was… June 26, 2020 In "News"